A simple gateway to store incoming email messages, and notify the intended recipient via c2dm.
The c2dm notification includes a url from which the rest of the message can be downloaded.

The intent is to use this gateway to deliver mail messages to Klaxon (http://code.google.com/p/klaxon).

C2DM docs: http://code.google.com/android/c2dm/

Useful URLS:
- /register - used by devices to register with the service.
  - Args: 
    - token - c2dm registration id.
    - sender - email address that is authorized to send c2dm messages.
- /test - debugging. sends a push message to the current user, assuming they are already registered.
- /admin - a simple interface to allow the inputting of credentials for the sender of C2dm messages.
  - *THESE CREDENTIALS ARE STORED IN THE APPENGINE DATASTORE*
  - you probably dont want to use your personal account.


The Anatomy of a C2dm Message:
- registration_id
- collapse_key
